org.apache.juneau.jena.annotation

Annotation Type Rdf


  • @Documented
 @Target(value={PACKAGE,TYPE,FIELD,METHOD})
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Inherited
public @interface Rdf
    Annotation for specifying options for RDF serializers.

    Can be applied to Java packages, types, fields, and methods.

    Can be used for the following:

    • Override the default behavior of how collections and arrays are serialized.

    • Element Detail

      • beanUri

        public abstract boolean beanUri
        Marks a bean property as a resource URI identifier for the bean.

        Has the following effects on the following serializers:

        • RdfSerializer - Will be rendered as the value of the "rdf:about" attribute for the bean.
        Default:
        false

      • collectionFormat

        public abstract RdfCollectionFormat collectionFormat
        The format for how collections (e.g. lists and arrays) are serialized in RDF.
        See Also:
        RdfCollectionFormat
        Default:
        org.apache.juneau.jena.RdfCollectionFormat.DEFAULT

      • namespace

        public abstract String namespace
        Sets the namespace URI of this property or class.

        Must be matched with a @Rdf.prefix() annotation on this object, a parent object, or a @RdfNs with the same name through the @RdfSchema.rdfNs() annotation on the package.

        Default:
        ""

      • prefix

        public abstract String prefix
        Sets the XML prefix of this property or class.

        Must either be matched to a @Rdf.namespace() annotation on the same object, parent object, or a @RdfNs with the same name through the @RdfSchema.rdfNs() annotation on the package.

        Default:
        ""
